{
  "stem": "521.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He mentioned to me that he was joining the war, the first World War, in 1914, and in 1915 he was in-- in a combat-- hand-to-hand combat-- and he was wounded in-- in the neck.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this wound healed, but I could see where he was pierced by a Russian soldier.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at that same time, he became a prisoner of war, and he was taken to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was there in a camp, and seemingly, the camp didn't have any fences, because it was several thousand miles away from Hungary.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So nobody was afraid that he was going to run away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was about 100, 150 kilometers from the Mongolian border.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was south of the Baikal Lake-- you know, where Irkutsk [INAUDIBLE] was.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was another lake, which they call it the [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Barlhas-- ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--which was a smaller lake.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No he wasn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was just a Hungarian prisoner of war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was no discrimination in those days.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And a prisoner of war is a prisoner.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was lucky, because he got acquainted with a farmer in Siberia whose son was a prisoner of war in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And according to my father, he said, I'm going to treat you well in the hope that where my son is a prisoner of war, he's treated-- will be treated or is treated by a Hungarian [? farmer ?] there someplace.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So he would-- There was an interesting incident.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father didn't know how to cook, but he got hold of some rice.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he was having a big pot, and filled-- filled it with rice, and put some-- and as you know, the rice is epanding real rapidly.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
